Pulverize the chocolate wafers and hazelnuts together in a food processor. Add the confectionersâ€™ sugar and process to combine. Dissolve the espresso in the Grand Marnier and add to the chocolate crumbs along with the com syrup. Process until the mixture forms a moist mass. Break off small pieces of the dough and roll them into 1-inch balls. Place the granulated sugar in a shallow bowl and roll each ball in the sugar to coat. Store loosely packed between layers of waxed paper in a cookie tin. Let age 1 week before serving.